---
import Admin from '@/layouts/Admin.astro';
---

<Admin
  title="Browser extension"
  intro="Qadan Apply Assist — a Manifest V3 Chrome extension that runs the apply agent on ATS forms. What it's allowed to do is set per session by autonomy level (L1 fill-only → L4 batch auto-apply); submits only happen at L3+ with dry-run off and every safety gate passing."
>
  <section class="ext">
    <article class="card">
      <h2>What it does</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Detects fields on Greenhouse, Lever, Ashby, Workday, SmartRecruiters, and LinkedIn Easy Apply forms</li>
        <li>Shows a preview of which fields it can autofill (high / medium / never confidence)</li>
        <li>Runs at the autonomy level you pick per session on <a href="/auto-apply">/auto-apply</a>:
          <strong>L1</strong> fill safe fields only · <strong>L2</strong> fill + auto-advance, pause before submit ·
          <strong>L3</strong> confirmed auto-submit when ALL gates pass · <strong>L4</strong> batch: processes the queue and submits eligible jobs</li>
        <li>Auto-submit (L3/L4) is gated: fit/authenticity/quality thresholds, daily + per-source caps, duplicate check, no CAPTCHA/login/legal/demographic blockers — and dry-run is ON by default</li>
        <li><strong>Never</strong> fills demographic, EEOC, work-auth-by-default, or salary fields</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Install (developer mode)</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Clone or download the <code>portfoliov2/extension</code> directory</li>
        <li>Open <code>chrome://extensions</code> in Chrome</li>
        <li>Toggle <strong>Developer mode</strong> (top right)</li>
        <li>Click <strong>Load unpacked</strong> and pick the <code>extension</code> directory</li>
        <li>Pin the extension to your toolbar</li>
      </ol>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Connect your vault</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Visit <a href="/vault">/vault</a> and fill the Profile Vault sections</li>
        <li>Click <strong>Export for extension</strong> and copy the JSON blob</li>
        <li>Click the extension icon → <strong>Import vault</strong> → paste the blob</li>
        <li>The extension now has your standard fields stored locally in <code>chrome.storage.local</code></li>
      </ol>
      <p class="muted">The extension never scrapes admin pages. Starting an agent session on /auto-apply pushes the vault to the extension as part of the session snapshot; the paste-import above is the manual fallback for popup-only use.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Daily use</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>From <a href="/auto-apply">/auto-apply</a>, pick jobs, pick an autonomy level, and start a session (L2 with dry-run on is the recommended default)</li>
        <li>The agent opens each listing, fills safe + packet fields, and auto-advances pages (L2+); filled cells get a yellow outline so you can see what changed</li>
        <li>At L1/L2 it pauses at the submit page and you click <strong>Submit</strong> yourself; at L3/L4 it submits only when every safety gate passes and dry-run is off</li>
        <li>Anything uncertain (CAPTCHA, login, unknown required fields, uploads it can't do) lands in <a href="/review">/review</a> with a reason — resolve and hit Retry</li>
        <li>Submitted attempts mark the job Applied automatically; manual one-off fills are still available from the extension popup</li>
      </ol>
    </article>

    <article class="card warning-card">
      <h2>What it will not do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Submit below L3, in dry-run mode, or past any failing gate (caps, duplicates, thresholds, legal/demographic blockers) — L4 only widens batching, never the gates</li>
        <li>Fill race, gender, ethnicity, disability, veteran, age, dateOfBirth, SSN, pronouns, religion fields — ever</li>
        <li>Auto-answer work authorization or sponsorship questions unless you explicitly enabled "Allow extension to autofill work-auth answers" in Vault</li>
        <li>Paste LLM-drafted answers without review below L3</li>
        <li>Solve CAPTCHAs</li>
        <li>Create accounts on your behalf</li>
        <li>Bypass any anti-bot protection</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>
</Admin>

<style>
  .ext { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 14px; }
  .ext h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 22px; font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .ext ol, .ext ul { padding-left: 22px; color: var(--c-text-muted); font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.7; }
  .ext code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px;
    background: var(--c-bg); padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 3px;
  }
  .ext a {
    color: var(--c-accent);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-border);
  }
  .muted { color: var(--c-text-subtle); font-size: 12px; margin-top: 8px; }
  .warning-card { border-color: rgba(248, 113, 113, 0.4); }
  .warning-card h2 { color: #FCA5A5; }
</style>
